
Pachalerts

Originally written to send Pachube triggers as Google Talk instant messages it should possible to use it
to send an IM to any XMPP client in response to a HTTP POST

Written in python to run on Google App Engine- makes extensive use of GAE's XMPP services

 
Try it out at http://pachalerts.appspot.com/

Notes:
Uses the Bottle framework for RESTful web interface http://bottlepy.org/

GAE XMPP docs http://code.google.com/appengine/docs/python/xmpp/overview.html


